{"TopicId":167158,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Serious Scientific Answers to Absurd Hypothetical questions","CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-03T20:21:11Z","PageNum":31,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T01:18:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538755\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549898817\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow hard and expensive would it be to fill a football stadium with water and have a ship battle?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy would you want a stadium, just find a large pond?\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 That\u0027s what they do in central Park......\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T01:49:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549934305\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy would you want a stadium, just find a large pond?\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 That\u0027s what they do in central Park......\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore seating...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T02:37:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539086\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549936163\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore seating...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you seen the loge box view of the pond in central park?? \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022191-12-manhattan-04.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022668\u0022 src=\u0022https://leadingestates.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/191-12-manhattan-04.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut seriously, a recently deceased member of the Model Boat Yacht Club I\u0027m in used to travel to Central Park a couple times a year to take part in Remote controlled recreations of famous naval battles.\u00A0\u00A0 The RC were all scale models of actual warships, usually ships of the line, with the only propulsion generated by the wind (ie they actually sailed, no motors), with functioning cannons they would shoot at each other.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut to flood a stadium, say an American football stadium, in order to host small sailing boat (like a Laser or FJ) would be fairly trivial. \u00A0 Just turn it into a huge above ground pool.\u00A0 Supported walls, and a liner covering the whole thing.\u00A0 The water would only have to be slightly deeper than the boats draft. \u00A0\u00A0 The downside would be wind.\u00A0 I\u0027ve raced in similarly sunken/sheltered ponds, and the wind is not steady, gusting and shifting constantly.\u00A0 Takes a lot of skill and a keen eye to read the wind shifts. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T02:40:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549939059\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you seen the loge box view of the pond in central park?? \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell no, I haven\u0027t Looks like luxury box seating for the senators...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T08:41:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538755\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549898817\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2019 at 6:26 PM, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow hard and expensive would it be to fill a football stadium with water and have a ship battle?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA quick glance through wikipedia says the Colliseum definitely lost the ability to stage naval combat when it got a huge basement. The innards of football fields are just as elaborate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo you\u2019d be looking at a major rebuild.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T08:41:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s the latent heat of fusion for anhydrous air??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T09:20:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550047271\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA quick glance through wikipedia says the Colliseum definitely lost the ability to stage naval combat when it got a huge basement.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s sad. We should design the future stadiums having in mind both gladiators and naumachia.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd Robot Jox as well. They probably match the constraints of a proper lake battle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/at7xEtjuewc/maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T14:05:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549939059\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2019 at 9:37 PM, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut to flood a stadium, say an American football stadium, in order to host small sailing boat (like a Laser or FJ) would be fairly trivial. \u00A0 Just turn it into a huge above ground pool.\u00A0 Supported walls, and a liner covering the whole thing.\u00A0 The water would only have to be slightly deeper than the boats draft. \u00A0\u00A0 The downside would be wind.\u00A0 I\u0027ve raced in similarly sunken/sheltered ponds, and the wind is not steady, gusting and shifting constantly.\u00A0 Takes a lot of skill and a keen eye to read the wind shifts. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t the NHL play hockey in such stadia?\u00A0 Of course, they hardly want a deep pond, and take the extra step of freezing it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539119\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549939247\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2019 at 9:40 PM, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell no, I haven\u0027t Looks like luxury box seating for the senators...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspect that plenty of people who live there expect senators to answer to them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T16:39:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550047291\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183478\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nivee~\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Nivee~ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s the latent heat of fusion\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E for anhydrous air??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom \u0022CRC Handbook of Chemistry and Physics\u0022 Ed.62, 1981-82:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHf (Nitrogen) - 6.15cal/g\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHf (Oxygen) - 3.3cal/g\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncalorie = 4.186J\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo Hf (air) would be roughly equal to 0.8(6.15) \u002B 0.2(3.3) = 5.58cal/g = 23.36J/g\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T16:42:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you need ~2*10\u003Csup\u003E9\u003C/sup\u003E K to start the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxygen-burning_process\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eoxygen fusion\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T18:41:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223540059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550076178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you need ~2*10\u003Csup\u003E9\u003C/sup\u003E K to start the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxygen-burning_process\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eoxygen fusion\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of my favorite articles:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://large.stanford.edu/courses/2015/ph241/chung1/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://large.stanford.edu/courses/2015/ph241/chung1/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-13T18:56:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223540124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550083269\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://large.stanford.edu/courses/2015/ph241/chung1/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://large.stanford.edu/courses/2015/ph241/chung1/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/kj4BpDyhFuE?start=271\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-14T00:04:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539994\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550066744\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t the NHL play hockey in such stadia?\u00A0 Of course, they hardly want a deep pond, and take the extra step of freezing it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut there\u0027s a fairly big difference in the structure required to keep 4 inches of ice in place, and 6 feet of water...\u00A0\u00A0 If you have a leak in the ice, you only need to plug it until it won\u0027t fit through the hole anymore.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T04:28:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there was a cave made of potatoes, what enzyme could I spray that would dissolve the potatoes and\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na) Not cause a fire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nb) Allow me to dig a tunnel wide enough to go through at a hundred feet a day\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc) Be easy to store\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T06:23:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow much armour penetration and beyond-armour effect could a thoroughly modern, dedicated war hammer have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00229E9845585690FA134733BBF9D1D39FDFAF1D9BFB\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/955226422220699543/9E9845585690FA134733BBF9D1D39FDFAF1D9BFB/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T07:42:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223542595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550464133\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there was a cave made of potatoes, what enzyme could I spray that would dissolve the potatoes and\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na) Not cause a fire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nb) Allow me to dig a tunnel wide enough to go through at a hundred feet a day\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nc) Be easy to store\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKetchup. You\u0027ll eat your way through the wall.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Piscator","CreatedById":107202,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T07:49:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t we have to know the type of armour first to assess the effectiveness of the hammer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T09:47:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223542636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550470981\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow much armour penetration and beyond-armour effect could a thoroughly modern, dedicated war hammer have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/955226422220699543/9E9845585690FA134733BBF9D1D39FDFAF1D9BFB/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00229E9845585690FA134733BBF9D1D39FDFAF1D9BFB\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/955226422220699543/9E9845585690FA134733BBF9D1D39FDFAF1D9BFB/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgainst body armor probably lot but also pretty overkill. Body armor is all or nothing, you try to protect the head and torso as good as possible. No armor outside of work cloth quality clothing other places.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWar hammers was only in use then full plate armor was as popular. Going forward and armor also started to go more all or nothing rather than full plate because of firearms, that made swords again work much better.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that above is an slege.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Warhammer-r-nagel.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/22/Warhammer-r-nagel.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022550\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis is an warhammer, granted an two handed one was larger but head was less than twice as heavy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-18T09:51:03Z\u0022 title=\u002202/18/2019 09:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 18, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by magnemoe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T10:01:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223542683\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550483241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou try to protect the head\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHead is bone. Let the enemy crash his hammer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223542683\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550483241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWar hammers was only in use then full plate armor was as popular.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuch ones for 5000 y or so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRIq05CH1KvJ3Qa9n_kFHP\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022156\u0022 src=\u0022https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRIq05CH1KvJ3Qa9n_kFHPGwNVQqXjC1oQ8J_MVlJO9ebL3RQQfbQ\u0022 width=\u0022323\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RizzoTheRat","CreatedById":123362,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T11:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModern ceramic armour plates can stop a 7.62 round at short range (google Stephen Tschiderer).\u00A0 A NATO 7.62 round leaves the muzzle with a about 3.5kJ of energy.\u00A0 Google suggests real war hammers weighed around 4lbs, so assuming 2kg, you\u0027d need to swing it at about 94 mph to hit with the same energy as a point blank 7.62.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparently an average golfer can hit the ball with the club head doing around 90mph, while a\u00A0pro can get up to 125mph.\u00A0 Given that a hammer\u0027s presumably going to have\u00A0a shorter handle than a golf club, and be at least 4 or 5 times the weight, I\u0027d have thought it unlikely anyone could swing one at 94mph.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T11:33:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223542696\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550488316\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123362\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RizzoTheRat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, RizzoTheRat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... unlikely anyone could swing one at 94mph.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost certainly not. That is in the range of a slow flying arrow to stay with the late medieval connotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022Streithammer\u0022 is a late medieval/early modern weapon that was meant to deform the armor (helmets had to fit closely and were lined with leather or they would dangle around the head) or to use the pointed side to poke through the soft parts at the joints in close combat or use as a lever. It is not the sole weapon, it would be useless against a long pointed sword (\u0022Panzerbrecher\u0022, \u0022Sempachschwert\u0022) because of slow speed (swing against thrust) or a halberd (lack of range).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll of these weapons would be pretty useless in modern times, except for sports or reenactment. Today people kill each other with drones, rockets, bombs, bullets, radioactivity, etc. pp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-18T11:38:50Z\u0022 title=\u002202/18/2019 11:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 18, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T11:41:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA warhammer war hammer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNotice the pikes concentrating the energy,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Hammer_Render2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i2.wp.com/vividfoundry.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Hammer_Render2.png\u0022 width=\u0022745\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same but on kitchen/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002258232fe463d0d440349a2bfc\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://media2.24aul.ru/imgs/58232fe463d0d440349a2bfc/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T11:49:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo your Schnitzels wear armour ? \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-18T12:13:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223542699\u0022 